job_history.work_description: Taught 9th grade, 11th grade and 12th grade English as well as AP Literature and AP Language. Developed curriculum to suit the needs of students at various ages.
Planned and scheduled monthly departmental meetings, allocated department funds, participated in the District Literacy Committee and disseminated information from administration to English teachers.
Prioritized student-leadership and facilitation, met with Senior ASB officers to discuss Leadership Development content and project management.

skills.name: Teaching
skills.explanation: Taught various English classes, including AP courses, and developed curriculum, indicating expert-level mastery.

skills.name: Curriculum Development
skills.explanation: Developed curriculum to suit the needs of students at various ages, showing strong proficiency.

skills.name: Leadership
skills.explanation: Held the position of Head Of English Department and ASB Advisor, indicating strong leadership skills.

skills.name: Project Management
skills.explanation: Facilitated project management as an ASB Advisor, showing a solid working proficiency.

skills.name: Communication
skills.explanation: Participated in departmental meetings and disseminated information from administration to English teachers, indicating a solid level of proficiency in communication.

skills.name: Team Management
skills.explanation: Allocated department funds and managed a team as the Head Of English Department, showing a solid working proficiency.
